{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"ad89a54ed84ed438d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are scanning the CLAUDE1-9 companion files for deep content relevant to the \"Telos Engine\" project.\n\nThese files are located at:\n- ~/CLAUDE1.md through ~/CLAUDE9.md\n\nRead each one and extract:\n\nFrom CLAUDE1.md (mech-interp technical):\n- TransformerLens patterns, activation patching methodology\n- Technical decisions and their rationale\n\nFrom CLAUDE2.md (Phoenix/URA):\n- Phoenix protocol details, L1-L5 levels\n- URA paper findings, 200+ trial results\n\nFrom CLAUDE3.md (contemplative framework):\n- Akram Vignan framework details\n- Jain metaphysics applied to computation\n- Witness/shuddhatma architecture\n\nFrom CLAUDE4.md (prompt engineering):\n- Prompt design principles relevant to agent architecture\n\nFrom CLAUDE5.md (code reference):\n- Validated scripts, canonical data paths\n\nFrom CLAUDE6.md (PSMV vault navigation):\n- Crown jewel locations in the vault\n\nFrom CLAUDE7.md (experimental results):\n- ALL numbers, ALL sources — the verified data\n\nFrom CLAUDE8.md (theoretical framework):\n- Eigenforms, recursive cosmology\n- Deep theoretical connections\n\nFrom CLAUDE9.md (session protocols):\n- Session management patterns\n\nFor each file, report:\n- Key ideas extracted (with specific content, not just topics)\n- Where content maps to in telos-engine/ (foundations/, research/, architecture/)\n- What's UNIQUE to this file that isn't elsewhere\n\nDO NOT write any code or create any files. This is RESEARCH ONLY."},"uuid":"12193b17-6b75-49b9-9651-6693680dd5e0","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:34.213Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
