{"parentUuid":"6e18b7e5-1d38-47fe-9157-b0db23970d39","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"ad89a54ed84ed438d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SYN4bqAzVALNobLfUHqy9o","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLAUDE5: Code Reference & Validated Scripts\n     2→**Version**: 2025-11-28 | **Type**: Complete Code Documentation\n     3→\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→## Overview\n     7→\n     8→This document contains all validated code for R_V measurement, activation patching, and analysis. These are the scripts that actually work - tested and confirmed.\n     9→\n    10→---\n    11→\n    12→## Core Functions\n    13→\n    14→### 1. Participation Ratio Computation\n    15→\n    16→**File**: `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/models/mistral_7b_analysis.py`\n    17→\n    18→```python\n    19→import torch\n    20→import numpy as np\n    21→\n    22→def compute_column_space_pr(v_tensor, window_size=16):\n    23→    \"\"\"\n    24→    Compute Participation Ratio from Value tensor.\n    25→\n    26→    The Participation Ratio (PR) measures effective dimensionality:\n    27→    PR = (Σλᵢ²)² / Σλᵢ⁴\n    28→\n    29→    Where λᵢ are singular values of the matrix.\n    30→\n    31→    Args:\n    32→        v_tensor: [seq_len, hidden_dim] Value projections\n    33→        window_size: Number of tokens from end to analyze\n    34→\n    35→    Returns:\n    36→        participation_ratio: float (effective dimensionality)\n    37→    \"\"\"\n    38→    # Extract window (last N tokens)\n    39→    seq_len = v_tensor.shape[0]\n    40→    start_idx = max(0, seq_len - window_size)\n    41→    V_window = v_tensor[start_idx:, :]\n    42→\n    43→    if V_window.shape[0] < 2:\n    44→        return np.nan\n    45→\n    46→    # SVD decomposition\n    47→    try:\n    48→        # Convert to float32 for numerical stability\n    49→        U, S, Vh = torch.linalg.svd(V_window.float(), full_matrices=False)\n    50→        S = S.cpu().numpy()\n    51→    except Exception as e:\n    52→        print(f\"SVD failed: {e}\")\n    53→        return np.nan\n    54→\n    55→    # Participation Ratio computation\n    56→    S_sq = S ** 2\n    57→    S_sq_sum = S_sq.sum()\n    58→\n    59→    if S_sq_sum == 0 or np.isnan(S_sq_sum):\n    60→        return np.nan\n    61→\n    62→    # PR = (Σλᵢ²)² / Σλᵢ⁴\n    63→    participation_ratio = (S_sq.sum() ** 2) / ((S_sq ** 2).sum())\n    64→\n    65→    return participation_ratio\n    66→```\n    67→\n    68→---\n    69→\n    70→### 2. V Matrix Capture Hook\n    71→\n    72→**File**: `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/models/mistral_7b_analysis.py`\n    73→\n    74→```python\n    75→from contextlib import contextmanager\n    76→\n    77→@contextmanager\n    78→def capture_v_at_layer(model, layer_idx, storage_list):\n    79→    \"\"\"\n    80→    Context manager to capture Value projections at a specific layer.\n    81→\n    82→    Uses forward hooks to intercept v_proj output during inference.\n    83→    Automatically cleans up hooks on exit.\n    84→\n    85→    Args:\n    86→        model: The transformer model\n    87→        layer_idx: Which layer to capture (0-indexed)\n    88→        storage_list: List to append captured tensors\n    89→\n    90→    Yields:\n    91→        None (tensors appended to storage_list)\n    92→    \"\"\"\n    93→    # Get the v_proj module for this layer\n    94→    layer = model.model.layers[layer_idx].self_attn\n    95→    handle = None\n    96→\n    97→    def hook_fn(module, inp, out):\n    98→        # Detach to avoid gradient tracking\n    99→        storage_list.append(out.detach())\n   100→        return out\n   101→\n   102→    # Register hook\n   103→    handle = layer.v_proj.register_forward_hook(hook_fn)\n   104→\n   105→    try:\n   106→        yield\n   107→    finally:\n   108→        # Always clean up hook\n   109→        if handle is not None:\n   110→            handle.remove()\n   111→```\n   112→\n   113→---\n   114→\n   115→### 3. Complete R_V Measurement Pipeline\n   116→\n   117→**File**: `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/models/mistral_7b_analysis.py`\n   118→\n   119→```python\n   120→def measure_r_v(prompt_text, model, tokenizer,\n   121→                target_layer=27, early_layer=5, window_size=16):\n   122→    \"\"\"\n   123→    Measure R_V = PR(V_target) / PR(V_early) for a single prompt.\n   124→\n   125→    R_V < 1.0 indicates geometric contraction (recursive signature)\n   126→    R_V ≈ 1.0 indicates no geometric change (baseline)\n   127→\n   128→    Args:\n   129→        prompt_text: The text prompt to analyze\n   130→        model: Loaded transformer model\n   131→        tokenizer: Corresponding tokenizer\n   132→        target_layer: Late layer for measurement (default: 27)\n   133→        early_layer: Early layer for reference (default: 5)\n   134→        window_size: Token window for PR computation\n   135→\n   136→    Returns:\n   137→        r_v: float (ratio of participation ratios)\n   138→    \"\"\"\n   139→    device = model.device\n   140→\n   141→    # Storage for captured activations\n   142→    v_early_list = []\n   143→    v_target_list = []\n   144→\n   145→    # Tokenize input\n   146→    inputs = tokenizer(prompt_text, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(device)\n   147→\n   148→    # Run forward pass with hooks\n   149→    with torch.no_grad():\n   150→        with capture_v_at_layer(model, early_layer, v_early_list):\n   151→            with capture_v_at_layer(model, target_layer, v_target_list):\n   152→                _ = model(**inputs)\n   153→\n   154→    # Extract captured tensors\n   155→    v_early = v_early_list[0][0] if v_early_list else None  # [seq, hidden]\n   156→    v_target = v_target_list[0][0] if v_target_list else None\n   157→\n   158→    if v_early is None or v_target is None:\n   159→        return np.nan\n   160→\n   161→    # Compute PR at each layer\n   162→    pr_early = compute_column_space_pr(v_early, window_size)\n   163→    pr_target = compute_column_space_pr(v_target, window_size)\n   164→\n   165→    # R_V ratio\n   166→    if pr_early > 0 and not np.isnan(pr_early):\n   167→        r_v = pr_target / pr_early\n   168→    else:\n   169→        r_v = np.nan\n   170→\n   171→    return r_v\n   172→```\n   173→\n   174→---\n   175→\n   176→### 4. Batch R_V Analysis\n   177→\n   178→```python\n   179→def analyze_prompt_bank(prompt_dict, model, tokenizer,\n   180→                        target_layer=27, early_layer=5):\n   181→    \"\"\"\n   182→    Run R_V measurement across a dictionary of prompts.\n   183→\n   184→    Args:\n   185→        prompt_dict: Dict with {prompt_id: {\"text\": str, \"group\": str}}\n   186→        model: Loaded model\n   187→        tokenizer: Tokenizer\n   188→\n   189→    Returns:\n   190→        results: List of dicts with {id, text, group, r_v}\n   191→    \"\"\"\n   192→    results = []\n   193→\n   194→    for prompt_id, prompt_data in prompt_dict.items():\n   195→        text = prompt_data[\"text\"]\n   196→        group = prompt_data.get(\"group\", \"unknown\")\n   197→\n   198→        r_v = measure_r_v(text, model, tokenizer,\n   199→                         target_layer=target_layer,\n   200→                         early_layer=early_layer)\n   201→\n   202→        results.append({\n   203→            \"id\": prompt_id,\n   204→            \"text\": text[:100] + \"...\" if len(text) > 100 else text,\n   205→            \"group\": group,\n   206→            \"r_v\": r_v\n   207→        })\n   208→\n   209→        print(f\"{prompt_id}: R_V = {r_v:.3f} ({group})\")\n   210→\n   211→    return results\n   212→```\n   213→\n   214→---\n   215→\n   216→## Activation Patching Code\n   217→\n   218→### 5. Validated Patching Script\n   219→\n   220→**File**: `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/R_V_PAPER/code/VALIDATED_mistral7b_layer27_activation_patching.py`\n   221→\n   222→```python\n   223→import torch\n   224→import numpy as np\n   225→from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n   226→\n   227→# Configuration\n   228→TARGET_LAYER = 27\n   229→EARLY_LAYER = 5\n   230→WINDOW_SIZE = 16\n   231→\n   232→def load_model():\n   233→    \"\"\"Load Mistral-7B with bfloat16 precision.\"\"\"\n   234→    model_name = \"mistralai/Mistral-7B-v0.1\"\n   235→\n   236→    model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n   237→        model_name,\n   238→        torch_dtype=torch.bfloat16,  # CRITICAL: float16 causes NaN\n   239→        device_map=\"auto\"\n   240→    )\n   241→    tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\n   242→\n   243→    return model, tokenizer\n   244→\n   245→\n   246→def capture_recursive_v(recursive_prompt, model, tokenizer):\n   247→    \"\"\"\n   248→    Run recursive prompt and capture Layer 27 V activations.\n   249→\n   250→    Returns:\n   251→        v_recursive: [seq_len, hidden_dim] tensor\n   252→    \"\"\"\n   253→    v_list = []\n   254→\n   255→    inputs = tokenizer(recursive_prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model.device)\n   256→\n   257→    def hook_fn(module, inp, out):\n   258→        v_list.append(out.detach())\n   259→        return out\n   260→\n   261→    layer = model.model.layers[TARGET_LAYER].self_attn\n   262→    handle = layer.v_proj.register_forward_hook(hook_fn)\n   263→\n   264→    with torch.no_grad():\n   265→        _ = model(**inputs)\n   266→\n   267→    handle.remove()\n   268→\n   269→    return v_list[0][0]  # [seq, hidden]\n   270→\n   271→\n   272→def patch_and_measure(baseline_prompt, recursive_v_source, model, tokenizer):\n   273→    \"\"\"\n   274→    Run baseline with Layer 27 V patched from recursive source.\n   275→\n   276→    The patching replaces the last WINDOW_SIZE positions of the\n   277→    baseline's V activations with those from the recursive prompt.\n   278→\n   279→    Returns:\n   280→        (r_v_patched, v_early, v_patched)\n   281→    \"\"\"\n   282→    v_early_list = []\n   283→    v_target_list = []\n   284→\n   285→    inputs = tokenizer(baseline_prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model.device)\n   286→\n   287→    # Early layer capture hook\n   288→    def early_hook(module, inp, out):\n   289→        v_early_list.append(out.detach())\n   290→        return out\n   291→\n   292→    # Patching hook at target layer\n   293→    def patch_hook(module, inp, out):\n   294→        out = out.clone()\n   295→        B, T, D = out.shape\n   296→\n   297→        # Source activations\n   298→        src = recursive_v_source.to(out.device, dtype=out.dtype)\n   299→        T_src = src.shape[0]\n   300→\n   301→        # Patch last WINDOW_SIZE positions\n   302→        k = min(WINDOW_SIZE, T, T_src)\n   303→        if k > 0:\n   304→            out[:, -k:, :] = src[-k:, :].unsqueeze(0)\n   305→\n   306→        v_target_list.append(out.detach()[0])\n   307→        return out  # Modified output propagates forward\n   308→\n   309→    # Register hooks\n   310→    early_layer = model.model.layers[EARLY_LAYER].self_attn\n   311→    target_layer = model.model.layers[TARGET_LAYER].self_attn\n   312→\n   313→    h_early = early_layer.v_proj.register_forward_hook(early_hook)\n   314→    h_patch = target_layer.v_proj.register_forward_hook(patch_hook)\n   315→\n   316→    # Run patched forward pass\n   317→    with torch.no_grad():\n   318→        _ = model(**inputs)\n   319→\n   320→    # Cleanup\n   321→    h_early.remove()\n   322→    h_patch.remove()\n   323→\n   324→    # Compute R_V\n   325→    v_early = v_early_list[0][0]\n   326→    v_patched = v_target_list[0]\n   327→\n   328→    pr_early = compute_column_space_pr(v_early, WINDOW_SIZE)\n   329→    pr_patched = compute_column_space_pr(v_patched, WINDOW_SIZE)\n   330→\n   331→    r_v_patched = pr_patched / pr_early if pr_early > 0 else np.nan\n   332→\n   333→    return r_v_patched, v_early, v_patched\n   334→\n   335→\n   336→def run_patching_experiment(recursive_prompts, baseline_prompts,\n   337→                            model, tokenizer):\n   338→    \"\"\"\n   339→    Run complete activation patching experiment.\n   340→\n   341→    For each (recursive, baseline) pair:\n   342→    1. Measure R_V of recursive prompt (natural)\n   343→    2. Measure R_V of baseline prompt (natural)\n   344→    3. Measure R_V of baseline with recursive V patched\n   345→    4. Calculate transfer = (patched - baseline)\n   346→\n   347→    Returns:\n   348→        results: List of dicts with all measurements\n   349→    \"\"\"\n   350→    results = []\n   351→\n   352→    for rec_prompt, base_prompt in zip(recursive_prompts, baseline_prompts):\n   353→        # Natural R_V for recursive\n   354→        r_v_rec = measure_r_v(rec_prompt, model, tokenizer,\n   355→                             TARGET_LAYER, EARLY_LAYER)\n   356→\n   357→        # Natural R_V for baseline\n   358→        r_v_base = measure_r_v(base_prompt, model, tokenizer,\n   359→                              TARGET_LAYER, EARLY_LAYER)\n   360→\n   361→        # Capture recursive V\n   362→        v_rec = capture_recursive_v(rec_prompt, model, tokenizer)\n   363→\n   364→        # Patched R_V\n   365→        r_v_patched, _, _ = patch_and_measure(base_prompt, v_rec,\n   366→                                              model, tokenizer)\n   367→\n   368→        # Compute transfer\n   369→        natural_gap = r_v_rec - r_v_base\n   370→        transfer = r_v_patched - r_v_base\n   371→        efficiency = (transfer / natural_gap * 100) if natural_gap != 0 else np.nan\n   372→\n   373→        results.append({\n   374→            \"rec_prompt\": rec_prompt[:50],\n   375→            \"base_prompt\": base_prompt[:50],\n   376→            \"r_v_rec\": r_v_rec,\n   377→            \"r_v_base\": r_v_base,\n   378→            \"r_v_patched\": r_v_patched,\n   379→            \"natural_gap\": natural_gap,\n   380→            \"transfer\": transfer,\n   381→            \"efficiency_pct\": efficiency\n   382→        })\n   383→\n   384→        print(f\"Rec: {r_v_rec:.3f}, Base: {r_v_base:.3f}, \"\n   385→              f\"Patched: {r_v_patched:.3f}, Transfer: {efficiency:.1f}%\")\n   386→\n   387→    return results\n   388→```\n   389→\n   390→---\n   391→\n   392→## Architecture-Specific Adaptations\n   393→\n   394→### 6. Pythia (GPT-NeoX) V Extraction\n   395→\n   396→**File**: `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/SUBSYSTEM_2D_MAP_COMPLETION/02_CODE/pythia_EXACT_MISTRAL_METHOD.py`\n   397→\n   398→```python\n   399→def get_pythia_v_at_layer(model, layer_idx, hidden_states):\n   400→    \"\"\"\n   401→    Extract V from Pythia's combined QKV projection.\n   402→\n   403→    GPT-NeoX uses combined query_key_value projection, not separate\n   404→    q_proj, k_proj, v_proj. Must split the output.\n   405→\n   406→    Args:\n   407→        model: Pythia model\n   408→        layer_idx: Layer index\n   409→        hidden_states: Input hidden states\n   410→\n   411→    Returns:\n   412→        v: [batch, seq, hidden] V projection\n   413→    \"\"\"\n   414→    layer = model.gpt_neox.layers[layer_idx]\n   415→    attn = layer.attention\n   416→\n   417→    # Combined QKV projection\n   418→    qkv = attn.query_key_value(hidden_states)\n   419→\n   420→    # Split into Q, K, V\n   421→    # Shape: [batch, seq, 3 * hidden_size]\n   422→    hidden_size = qkv.shape[-1] // 3\n   423→\n   424→    q = qkv[..., :hidden_size]\n   425→    k = qkv[..., hidden_size:2*hidden_size]\n   426→    v = qkv[..., 2*hidden_size:]  # Last third is V\n   427→\n   428→    return v\n   429→\n   430→\n   431→@contextmanager\n   432→def capture_pythia_v_at_layer(model, layer_idx, storage_list):\n   433→    \"\"\"\n   434→    Context manager for Pythia V capture.\n   435→\n   436→    Hooks into query_key_value and extracts V portion.\n   437→    \"\"\"\n   438→    layer = model.gpt_neox.layers[layer_idx]\n   439→    handle = None\n   440→\n   441→    def hook_fn(module, inp, out):\n   442→        # out is combined QKV\n   443→        hidden_size = out.shape[-1] // 3\n   444→        v = out[..., 2*hidden_size:]  # Extract V\n   445→        storage_list.append(v.detach())\n   446→        return out\n   447→\n   448→    handle = layer.attention.query_key_value.register_forward_hook(hook_fn)\n   449→\n   450→    try:\n   451→        yield\n   452→    finally:\n   453→        if handle is not None:\n   454→            handle.remove()\n   455→```\n   456→\n   457→---\n   458→\n   459→### 7. Model Loading Best Practices\n   460→\n   461→```python\n   462→def load_model_safe(model_name):\n   463→    \"\"\"\n   464→    Load model with correct precision and settings.\n   465→\n   466→    CRITICAL: Must use bfloat16 for deep layer stability.\n   467→    float16 causes NaN at layers 25+.\n   468→    \"\"\"\n   469→    from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n   470→\n   471→    model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n   472→        model_name,\n   473→        torch_dtype=torch.bfloat16,  # NOT float16\n   474→        device_map=\"auto\",\n   475→        trust_remote_code=True  # For some models\n   476→    )\n   477→\n   478→    tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\n   479→\n   480→    # Set pad token if needed\n   481→    if tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n   482→        tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n   483→\n   484→    model.eval()  # Always eval mode for inference\n   485→\n   486→    return model, tokenizer\n   487→```\n   488→\n   489→---\n   490→\n   491→## Utility Functions\n   492→\n   493→### 8. Statistical Analysis\n   494→\n   495→```python\n   496→from scipy import stats\n   497→\n   498→def analyze_results(recursive_rvs, baseline_rvs):\n   499→    \"\"\"\n   500→    Compute statistical comparison between groups.\n   501→\n   502→    Returns:\n   503→        dict with t-stat, p-value, Cohen's d, means, stds\n   504→    \"\"\"\n   505→    rec = np.array([r for r in recursive_rvs if not np.isnan(r)])\n   506→    base = np.array([r for r in baseline_rvs if not np.isnan(r)])\n   507→\n   508→    # t-test\n   509→    t_stat, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(rec, base)\n   510→\n   511→    # Cohen's d\n   512→    pooled_std = np.sqrt((rec.std()**2 + base.std()**2) / 2)\n   513→    cohens_d = (rec.mean() - base.mean()) / pooled_std\n   514→\n   515→    return {\n   516→        \"n_recursive\": len(rec),\n   517→        \"n_baseline\": len(base),\n   518→        \"mean_recursive\": rec.mean(),\n   519→        \"mean_baseline\": base.mean(),\n   520→        \"std_recursive\": rec.std(),\n   521→        \"std_baseline\": base.std(),\n   522→        \"t_statistic\": t_stat,\n   523→        \"p_value\": p_value,\n   524→        \"cohens_d\": cohens_d\n   525→    }\n   526→```\n   527→\n   528→---\n   529→\n   530→### 9. Results Saving\n   531→\n   532→```python\n   533→import csv\n   534→from datetime import datetime\n   535→\n   536→def save_results_csv(results, prefix=\"experiment\"):\n   537→    \"\"\"\n   538→    Save experiment results to timestamped CSV.\n   539→    \"\"\"\n   540→    timestamp = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")\n   541→    filename = f\"{prefix}_{timestamp}.csv\"\n   542→\n   543→    if not results:\n   544→        return None\n   545→\n   546→    fieldnames = results[0].keys()\n   547→\n   548→    with open(filename, 'w', newline='') as f:\n   549→        writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=fieldnames)\n   550→        writer.writeheader()\n   551→        writer.writerows(results)\n   552→\n   553→    print(f\"Saved to {filename}\")\n   554→    return filename\n   555→```\n   556→\n   557→---\n   558→\n   559→## Complete Experiment Script\n   560→\n   561→### 10. End-to-End R_V Experiment\n   562→\n   563→```python\n   564→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n   565→\"\"\"\n   566→Complete R_V measurement experiment.\n   567→\n   568→Usage:\n   569→    python run_rv_experiment.py --model mistral --prompts recursive\n   570→\"\"\"\n   571→\n   572→import argparse\n   573→import torch\n   574→from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n   575→\n   576→# Import prompt bank\n   577→import sys\n   578→sys.path.append('/Users/dhyana/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1')\n   579→from n300_mistral_test_prompt_bank import prompt_bank_1c\n   580→\n   581→\n   582→def main():\n   583→    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n   584→    parser.add_argument('--model', default='mistral',\n   585→                       choices=['mistral', 'pythia', 'llama'])\n   586→    parser.add_argument('--groups', nargs='+',\n   587→                       default=['L5_refined', 'baseline_long'])\n   588→    args = parser.parse_args()\n   589→\n   590→    # Model mapping\n   591→    MODEL_NAMES = {\n   592→        'mistral': 'mistralai/Mistral-7B-v0.1',\n   593→        'pythia': 'EleutherAI/pythia-2.8b',\n   594→        'llama': 'meta-llama/Llama-3.2-8B'\n   595→    }\n   596→\n   597→    print(f\"Loading {args.model}...\")\n   598→    model, tokenizer = load_model_safe(MODEL_NAMES[args.model])\n   599→\n   600→    # Filter prompts by group\n   601→    prompts = {k: v for k, v in prompt_bank_1c.items()\n   602→               if v.get('group') in args.groups}\n   603→\n   604→    print(f\"Analyzing {len(prompts)} prompts...\")\n   605→    results = analyze_prompt_bank(prompts, model, tokenizer)\n   606→\n   607→    # Statistics by group\n   608→    for group in args.groups:\n   609→        group_rvs = [r['r_v'] for r in results if r['group'] == group]\n   610→        mean_rv = np.nanmean(group_rvs)\n   611→        std_rv = np.nanstd(group_rvs)\n   612→        print(f\"\\n{group}: R_V = {mean_rv:.3f} ± {std_rv:.3f}\")\n   613→\n   614→    # Save results\n   615→    save_results_csv(results, f\"rv_{args.model}\")\n   616→\n   617→    print(\"\\nDone!\")\n   618→\n   619→\n   620→if __name__ == '__main__':\n   621→    main()\n   622→```\n   623→\n   624→---\n   625→\n   626→## Code File Locations\n   627→\n   628→### Validated Scripts\n   629→\n   630→| Script | Path | Status |\n   631→|--------|------|--------|\n   632→| Prompt Bank | `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/n300_mistral_test_prompt_bank.py` | ✅ |\n   633→| Mistral Analysis | `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/models/mistral_7b_analysis.py` | ✅ |\n   634→| Activation Patching | `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/R_V_PAPER/code/VALIDATED_mistral7b_layer27_activation_patching.py` | ✅ |\n   635→| Pythia Adaptation | `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/SUBSYSTEM_2D_MAP_COMPLETION/02_CODE/pythia_EXACT_MISTRAL_METHOD.py` | ✅ |\n   636→\n   637→### Utility Modules\n   638→\n   639→| Module | Path | Functions |\n   640→|--------|------|-----------|\n   641→| IO Utils | `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/utils/io.py` | `set_seed_all`, `save_jsonl`, `stamp` |\n   642→| Metrics | `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/utils/metrics.py` | `epsilon_last_token`, `attn_entropy_lastrow` |\n   643→\n   644→---\n   645→\n   646→## Common Issues and Fixes\n   647→\n   648→### Issue: NaN at Deep Layers\n   649→\n   650→```python\n   651→# WRONG\n   652→model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(..., torch_dtype=torch.float16)\n   653→\n   654→# CORRECT\n   655→model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(..., torch_dtype=torch.bfloat16)\n   656→```\n   657→\n   658→### Issue: Hooks Not Removed\n   659→\n   660→```python\n   661→# WRONG\n   662→handle = layer.register_forward_hook(hook_fn)\n   663→# ... forget to remove\n   664→\n   665→# CORRECT - use context manager\n   666→with capture_v_at_layer(model, layer, storage):\n   667→    output = model(**inputs)\n   668→# Hook automatically removed\n   669→```\n   670→\n   671→### Issue: Short Prompts Fail Patching\n   672→\n   673→```python\n   674→# WRONG - prompt shorter than window\n   675→baseline = \"What is 2+2?\"  # ~6 tokens\n   676→\n   677→# CORRECT - use long prompts\n   678→baseline = \"Explain the complete history...\"  # 60+ tokens\n   679→```\n   680→\n   681→### Issue: Wrong R_V Definition\n   682→\n   683→```python\n   684→# WRONG - measuring at downstream layer\n   685→r_v = pr_layer31 / pr_layer5\n   686→\n   687→# CORRECT - measure at patch point\n   688→r_v = pr_layer27 / pr_layer5\n   689→```\n   690→\n   691→---\n   692→\n   693→## Quick Code Reference\n   694→\n   695→```python\n   696→# Load model\n   697→model, tokenizer = load_model_safe(\"mistralai/Mistral-7B-v0.1\")\n   698→\n   699→# Measure single prompt\n   700→r_v = measure_r_v(\"Your prompt here\", model, tokenizer)\n   701→\n   702→# Run patching experiment\n   703→results = run_patching_experiment(\n   704→    recursive_prompts=[\"Sx = x...\"],\n   705→    baseline_prompts=[\"Long factual...\"],\n   706→    model=model,\n   707→    tokenizer=tokenizer\n   708→)\n   709→\n   710→# Analyze statistics\n   711→stats = analyze_results(recursive_rvs, baseline_rvs)\n   712→print(f\"Cohen's d: {stats['cohens_d']:.2f}\")\n   713→```\n   714→\n   715→---\n   716→\n   717→*CLAUDE5.md - Code Reference & Validated Scripts*\n   718→*Generated: 2025-11-28*\n   719→*Status: All code tested and working*\n   720→"}]},"uuid":"f6843510-c293-42d5-8a9b-bfdbf3da0913","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:36.705Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6e18b7e5-1d38-47fe-9157-b0db23970d39","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
